  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scaling up successful project that Develops Libraries and Reading Centres to Rural Schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recent tests of primary school children in Ethiopia have revealed high levels of illiteracy and very poor reading ability in rural schools. This project scales up the successful work of a pilot intervention that improved students&apos; access to books and other reading material through libraries, teacher training and the production of low cost sets of books for teacher and class use. The books are produced by disabled people and contain lessons on disability and health care. The project aims to improve literacy and help people enjoy better health, as well as breaking down some of the stigma around disability in Ethiopia.</narrative>
  </description>
